passages.text:
//Why? Why did it have to be like this?//
//I was happy. I was sincerely happy.//
//How did it turn out like this?//
//Why now?//
Lying down in fetus position, glossy tears drip down on the bed. Clutching your chest, you feel like it is the end of the world. Your heart is beating so fast that it is as if it is going to burst out of your chest. You feel bags under your eyes from the lack of sleep and boogers forming at the corners from all of the crying. You feel the puffiness around your once doe-eyed eyes and snot coming out of your nose. You feel a migraine coming, but it is impossible to sleep it off. All you can do is cry yourself to sleep in the dark room alone.

[[Continue|after_First]]

//Knock knock//
"..."
//Knock knock//
"..."
"Tammi, I know you're in there" Kaylee, your best friend and former roommate from your freshman year of college calmly said.
"..."
//Creak//
You hear the door open and footsteps coming in. Normally, the sound of a creaky door open scares the living life out of you, but today, you are like a lifeless human being.
"Tammi, it's 3 A.M. I know you've been crying."
//Sniff//
"I'm sorry," you barely whisper while sniffling. "I'll try to be quieter."
"It's not that. It's just I'm worried about you."
[[Continue|after_First1]]

//I wish I can take a walk so I wouldn't disturb anyone.//
You have the urge to go on an early morning walk, but you are in a foreign country staying at Kaylee's father's house. Plus, you do not know the language, and you are terrible at directions. All you can do is try to fall asleep and not think about //him//.
//I miss him, yet I feel hurt on what he did to me.//
Every time you try to close your eyes, you think of //him// and end up in even more tears. The feeling is killing you, and you can't help it. This is officially the worst summer ever.
You want to contact him since even though it is 3 A.M. where you are now, it is 6P.M. where he is back in America. You have enough data to Facebook message him or use the video chat feature in the app, but you don't have the strength to write a simple message.
//I want to see you.//
[[Continue|after_First3]]

Switching sides, you cannot find a nice position to fall asleep. You were always known to move too much in your sleep whenever you are at a sleepover at your cousins, but this was something else. 
//Why can't I worry about something else, like whether or not I even passed any of the classes I took over summer?//
//I feel like a depressed teenager, but worse.//
You faintly recall the time when you were depressed due to bullying in high school, but compared to now, bullying meant nothing. This is your first relationship, and you were happy until now.
Closing, your eyes once more, you try to see if thinking about the good times will ease the pain. 
//I remember how we met, though it wasn't that interesting.//

[[Flashback|Flashback1]]
[[No, it's too painful|after_First4]]

Thinking back on the memory of first meeting, you are able to let out a tiny chuckle because you thought that Cooper was way more interesting and good-looking. 
You remember that since he lived in the same building as you, he visited so many times.
//I didn't think he'd still visit even after Cooper had to go back to his college.//
Your give out a small smile because you remember the feeling of surprise whenever he knocked on your door. Ever since you and your two roommates got in trouble with the supervisors of the building due to being too loud, the sound of the door knocking scared every one. 
//I can't believe we got written up. I have never even gotten a detention in my life!//
[[Continue|after_Flashback1-Reality1]]

//Maybe being in the same room as Kaylee will make me want to try even harder to sleep.//
You remember how your parents always taught you that crying in front of people was a no-no, so you have been trying to control crying in public ever since.
You softly tip-toe to the door to Kaylee's room like a ninja and open the door.
//At least the door isn't closed all the way.//
You open the door as little as you can to slip in and quickly close the door to remove the light. You cannot see anything and realize that you left your phone in the other room.
//Should I quickly grab it?//
[[No. You might end up making more noise than you should.|Stay_In_Kaylee_Room]]

[[Yes. You might end up crashing into something when going to the bed and wake up Kaylee.|Go_Bck_Get_Phone]]

//Wow! I've never been through this path before.//
You take in every nook and cranny as you swivel your head around your surroundings. The bright summer weather makes the scenery look even ten times better. You look up to see trees as tall as skyscrapers. It is silent except the sound of shoes walking carefully on the stone-carved stairs.
//Oh, this will definitely be scary to cross when it's raining.//
You look behind you to find Cooper taking numerous photos of the beautiful trees and forest. 
Looking ahead, you see James slightly in front of you. You notice how tall he is compared to your small stature as you have to look up just to check out his hair, which just adds to his height since it sticks up.
After admiring James for ten seconds, you look back again to check up on the guest.
//Still taking pictures? Haha. It's like he's never been outside before//
After walking through the forest with a long moment of silence, you wonder whether you should strike up a conversation with James since you live in the same dorm house and have the same major.
[[Continue|Flashback_First_Anime3]]

As you try to go back to sleep, you have the sudden urge to use the bathroom. 
//Really?//
After all the strength it took you just to close the door, you feel like it is nearly impossible to walk all the way down the hall and down the stairs to reach the toilet.
//Not that I can help it, I guess.//
You are a little faster in getting up and opening the door this time since you actually have to use the toilet and relieve yourself, but once you reach the bathroom, you are out of breathe. You lean on the side of the bathroom door before turning on the light and proceed to use the bathroom.
[[Continue|After_Second_Flashback_part2]]

After you finish your business, you stay on the toilet staring into space. 
Before completely drifting off, you shake your head violently to wake yourself up.
//I should head back to the room.//

//Should I head back to bed in Kaylee's room, or should I still try to sleep in the same room?//

[[Head back to Kaylee's room. Maybe you'll get enough sleep?|Kaylee_room_after_toilet]]
[[Head back to the same room. I don't want to disturb her.|Same_room_after_toilet]]

//Having someone sleeping next to me might help a bit.// Immediately, you miss your loyal, adorable dog who loves to sleep right next to you on the bed.
You sneak into the room trying not to wake Kaylee up and swifty make your way to the bed.

[[Continue|Flashback_Num_2]]

//I don't want to disturb her. I should just stay in the other room.//
You wash your hands with the cold water and wipe them on your loose shirt. Still pretty tired, you drag your feet on the freezing wooden floor back to the room. Before you open the door to go back to the room, you notice the mirror Kaylee begged her father to buy yesterday. It was hanging in the middle of the room you are staying in and the room Kaylee is sleeping in. 
//Wow. I look like a hot mess.//
You bring your right hand up and gently touch the mounds of puffiness that all of your crying caused. 
//Ouch! It stings a little.//
You leave the mound surrounding the bottom of your eye alone and droop your hand you your cheek and bring it down to massage your face.
//My entire face hurts. Whatever.//
You try to look at your face profile using the mirror, and your slim face lost its shape and has turned to a plumpy tomato. 
//I hope this goes away in the morning.//
[[Continue|Same_room_after_toilet_pt2]]

You continue to head back to the room and bury your face in the shivering sheets.
//I have three hours to sleep. I guess I can catch up on sleep in the car.//
You try to go to sleep again, but after using the toilet, you are more awake than before.
//I guess I can go on the internet.//
At this point, you don't care about your data limit.
//I'll just purchase another data card and reload it.//
[[Continue|Same_room_after_toilet_pt3]]

//Are summer grades out yet?// You go online to check your grades, but none of them are out yet.
//I mean, it's not like I'm worried if I failed. Well, maybe one class, but that's it.//
You check to see when grades are supposed to be out by.
//Oh, in four days. Seems so far away.//
You scoot your phone under your pillow and try to sleep after geting that out of the way. Before you know it, you are knocked out.

[[Continue|After_Flashback_Confession]]

//I should get my phone so I can see better.//
You walk back to the previous room and notice a green light blinking in the room of darkness.
//Uh-oh.//
You know that familiar color of notification.
//It's him.//
[[Check your phone.|Check_phone_for_message]]
[[On second thought, you don't need your phone.|back_to_kayleeRoom]]

//No! No, don't do it, Tammi.// You can feel the temptation overcoming you, but you just can't go through with it. For your own good.

//I should just go back. Not like I need my phone, anyway.// You were about to leave again, but you realize you still need your phone for checking the time so you can get ready on time in the morning since you are the one who takes the longest to get ready.

//Darn it//

[[Continue|Darn_It]]

''If I'm so easy to read, how is it that I'm in this mess in the first place?''
//Ah, should I really have sent him that?//
You are second-guessing your choice in words, thinking that it may be a bit severe. 
//I should probably take it back.// As you were typing in an apology, he beat you to the messaging.
''I'm sorry. :(''
You feel tears starting to erupt, skewing your vision of the messaging screen. 
//When will the pain disappear?//
All of a sudden, your phone vibrates. You don't need to look at the screen to see what the commotion is. 
//He really is a nice guy.//

[[Continue|Answer_Phone]]

You decide that you are bored and that you will most likely wake up cranky and be the killjoy of the group, so you use that as your motivation to go back to bed.
//This is my vacation. I must cherish it, even if I'm feeling blue.//

[[Continue|Flashback_Num_2]]

//Didn't know how to tell me? You weren't hesitant when you kept on putting me down. You're lucky I just laughed it off, you jerk!//
"Didn't know how to tell me? You are seemingly good at putting me down!"
//Oh, I basically said that.//
"I'm sorry! I shouldn't have done that. I shou-"

All of a sudden, you hear a scream, which woke you from your dream. All you can see is a big rig coming right at you before everything turns black once more.

[[Continue|Done_1]]

//What a lovely memory.// You are able to sleep a bit better after that small trip down memory lane and fall asleep. 
Once morning came, you felt a little groggy, but apparently, you are visiting another city by car, and it takes about three hours to get there.
//More sleep time, I guess.//

[[Continue|After_Flashback_Confession]]
